						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Parāntaka I, Year 27 = 934 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gift of gold for a lamp by a native of Kiḷinallūr in Kiḻār-kūṟṟam. The money was entrusted to the <hi rend="italic">panniraṇḍu-nāṭṭu-sabhai</hi> of Tiruchcheṅgōḍu, while the people of the ‘eighteen districts’ were to protect the grant.</p>						

